Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Afghanistan are 9 down now. A soft dismissal for Nijat Masood. Bowls a full toss on the middle, Nijat Masood hits it straight to the bowler holding his pose, and dollies a catch to Asitha Fernando who grabs it nicely on his follow-through. A dramatic collapse for Afghanistan.
Default_Commentary: 62.2: Asitha Fernando to Nijat Masood, OUT! c & b Asitha Fernando.

Commentary: An appeal by the keeper and the bowler for LBW and Dhananjaya de Silva goes upstairs after chatting with the fielders just before the clock runs out. Cannons a fantastic fuller-length ball on the leg stump line that slants across leg, Mohammad Saleem clears his front foot to go big over the leg side with a wild swing of the bat, but the ball passes through his inside edge. The keeper thinks that there is some noise. The UltraEdge comes up and shows that no bat is involved when the ball passes the bat before carrying to the keeper. NOT OUT.
Default_Commentary: 62.3: Asitha Fernando to Mohammad Saleem, No run.

Commentary: OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! BULL'S EYE! And it's curtains for Afghanistan. Guns a fantastic yorker on the off stump line, Mohammad Saleem looks to play it late but gets beaten by the pace. The ball bamboozles the off-pole. Sri Lanka have managed to bundle out Afghanistan below 200. Asitha Fernando finishes with an excellent 3-fer.
Default_Commentary: 62.4: Asitha Fernando to Mohammad Saleem, OUT! b Asitha Fernando.

Commentary: Is there an edge? Has that bounced after hitting the bat? Lanka do feel there is an edge and it has bounced before. Review taken. By the first replay, it seems to have missed the bat. Ultra Edge coming up. OUT! The umpire feels there is a clear deviation and Nijat Masood has to walk back. Good review in the end. It was a tough one for the umpire and he rules it in favor of Lanka. Fuller and around off, Nijat Masood looks to jam it out but there is a noise as the ball passes the bat. Ultra Edge does show a spike but the bat is also hitting the ground. There though is a deviation as it passes the bat. Number 9 down.
